You can create this exact PrimeNG-style Export to Excel button (without dropdown) using a p-button with an icon and a green background.

Here’s an example:

<p-button 
    label="Export" 
    icon="pi pi-file-excel" 
    styleClass="p-button-success" 
    (onClick)="exportToExcel()">
</p-button>

If you want it exactly like the screenshot (Excel icon + green rounded rectangle, no dropdown), use custom CSS with PrimeNG:

<button pButton 
        type="button" 
        class="excel-btn" 
        (click)="exportToExcel()">
    <i class="pi pi-file-excel"></i>
    <span>Export</span>
</button>

.excel-btn {
    background-color: #21a366 !important; /* Excel green */
    border: none;
    border-radius: 8px; /* rounded corners */
    padding: 8px 16px;
    color: white;
    font-weight: 500;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
}

.excel-btn:hover {
    background-color: #1e8b57 !important;
}

This will give you a non-dropdown button styled exactly like the image you sent.

If you want, I can make it with the real Excel SVG icon instead of PrimeNG’s pi-file-excel so it looks pixel-perfect like your screenshot. Do you want me to make that version?

